Name: primary spontaneous pneumothorax
Definition: A lipid storage disease characterized by lysosomal and lipase deficiency.
Synonym: Primary mediastinal clear cell lymphoma of B-cell type

Name: spontaneous tension pneumothorax
Definition: An embryonal cancer that are masses of rapidly growing cells that originates in embryonic (fetal) tissue in the brain and spinal cord.

Name: hemopneumothorax
Definition: An autosomal recessive disease characterized by sun sensitivity

Name: tuberculous pneumothorax
Definition: A pneumothorax in which air enters into the pleural cavity.

Name: obsolete Arenavirus hemorrhagic fever
Definition: A viral infectious disease that involves fever and bleeding disorder caused by Arenavirus.
